theorem interior_closure_union_interior_closure_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure ((A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X))) : Set X)) =
      interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
  -- First, show that taking the closure does not change after adding
  -- `interior (closure A)` to `A`.
  have h_subset :
      ((A : Set X) ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆
        closure (A : Set X) := by
    intro x hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hxA   => exact subset_closure hxA
    | inr hxInt => exact interior_subset hxInt
  have h_cl_eq :
      closure ((A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X))) : Set X) =
        closure (A : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact closure_mono h_subset
    · -- Conversely, `A` is contained in the union, hence so are their closures.
      have h_incl : (A : Set X) ⊆
          (A : Set X) ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
        intro x hx; exact Or.inl hx
      exact closure_mono h_incl
  -- Rewriting with the equality of closures yields the desired identity.
  simpa [h_cl_eq]

theorem closure_union_interior_closure_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure ((A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X))) : Set X) ⊆
      closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- First, prove the underlying inclusion without `closure`.
  have hSub :
      (A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆
        closure (A : Set X) := by
    intro x hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hxA =>
        -- Points from `A` are, by definition, in `closure A`.
        exact subset_closure hxA
    | inr hxInt =>
        -- Points from `interior (closure A)` lie in `closure A`
        -- because the interior is contained in the set itself.
        exact interior_subset hxInt
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  exact closure_mono hSub

theorem closure_iInter_interiors_subset_iInter_closure_interiors
    {X ι : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {F : ι → Set X} :
    closure (⋂ i, interior (F i : Set X)) ⊆ ⋂ i, closure (interior (F i : Set X)) := by
  intro x hx
  -- For each `i`, we show `x ∈ closure (interior (F i))`.
  have h : ∀ i, x ∈ closure (interior (F i : Set X)) := by
    intro i
    -- The set `⋂ i, interior (F i)` is contained in `interior (F i)`.
    have hSubset :
        (⋂ j, interior (F j : Set X)) ⊆ interior (F i : Set X) :=
      Set.iInter_subset _ _
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
    have hCl :
        closure (⋂ j, interior (F j : Set X)) ⊆
          closure (interior (F i : Set X)) :=
      closure_mono hSubset
    exact hCl hx
  -- Assemble the memberships into an element of the intersection.
  exact Set.mem_iInter.mpr h
